{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2754", "repo": "rails", "body": "Might want to wrap that in a `begin/rescue` block? Like:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\ndef has_secure_password\r\n  begin\r\n    gem 'bcrypt-ruby', '~> 3.0.0'\r\n    require 'bcrypt'\r\n  rescue LoadError\r\n    # give meaningful error about bcrypt\r\n  end\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like `ActiveRecord::Base` includes this file by default and it is always loaded, so we can't put it at the top of the file. My first idea was to put it in `has_secure_password` as well.", "_id": {"$oid": "52384089bd3543c1510108c2"}, "issue_id": 2754, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1967018", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2754#issuecomment-1967018", "updated_at": "2011-09-01T11:12:13Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman", "login": "tieleman", "gravatar_id": "c8227bc87233869147276b1952f016cc", "html_url": "https://github.com/tieleman", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/c8227bc87233869147276b1952f016cc?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe2e57ded5b59a2058dd5855564c6b5ea.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 28905, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tieleman/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-09-01T11:12:13Z", "id": 1967018, "owner": "rails"}
